Home/ Careers




Careers  Bellatrix Exploration is a growth oriented exploration and production company located in Calgary, Alberta. We recognize that our success is driven by the strength and dedication of the members of our team of management and employees. If you have the drive and desire to belong to a dynamic, team-oriented corporate culture, and the skills needed to work in a fast-paced and challenging work environment, we invite you to apply for the jobs posted below. 









Job TitleJob Description



Future Opportunities
Job Description


Senior Analyst - Business Development
Job Description






 Please send a cover letter, and resume to: careers@bxe.com   RECRUITMENT SCAMS It has come to our attention that individuals and/or organizations have been falsely using Bellatrix’s name to give employment offers, and/or to request money or personal information. Bellatrix does not use recruiting or placement agencies that charge candidates a fee of any kind, including, but not limited to, placement fees or immigration processing fees. Although we do periodically work with recruitment agencies to find potential candidates for specific positions at our own expense, at no point in the recruiting process would an applicant be asked to pay a fee.  In addition, interviews would most likely take place at one of Bellatrix’s offices with a Bellatrix employee present.  Here are some warning signs that may indicate fraud and/or a recruitment scam:  Unsolicited emails from web-based email accounts such as Gmail, Hotmail, Yahoo or Wildblue.net A request for financial/banking information or passport/visa information, or a request to pay any fees An offer of employment for locations not disclosed on the Bellatrix website Poor grammar or spelling used in correspondence  If you are unsure whether you have been a victim of a recruiting scam, please contact: careers@bxe.com. To report a recruitment scam, or if you have sent money or personal information and need assistance, please contact: For Canada – Visit the Canada Anti-Fraud Centre (CAFC) website or call 1-888-495-8501. 
For United States – Visit the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) website.








