Bellatrix Exploration Ltd Ordin (NYSE:BXE) Sees Light Trading Volume with 5,766 Shares Changing Hands 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsBellatrix Exploration Ltd Ordin (NYSE:BXE) Sees Light Trading Volume with 5,766 Shares Changing Hands
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



(NYSE:BXE) shares saw light trading volume with 5,766 shares changing hands by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 99.84% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in BXE.   Morgan Stanley trimmed its position by selling 509,736 shares a decrease of 93.4% in the quarter. Morgan Stanley now holds 36,000 shares with a value of $29,000. The value of the position overall is down by 94.4%. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) bolstered its holdings by buying 3,271 shares an increase of 48.8% as of 03/31/2017. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) claims 9,971 shares worth $10,000. The total value of its holdings increased 11.1%.
 Schroder Investment Management Group expanded its ownership by buying 3,144,549 shares an increase of 20.6%. Schroder Investment Management Group owns 18,442,118 shares valued at $19,180,000. The value of the position overall is down by 2.0%. As of the end of the quarter Muhlenkamp & Co Inc had sold 8,165 shares trimming its position 1.4%. The value of the company’s investment in Bellatrix Exploration Ltd Ordin decreased from $565,000 to $469,000 a change of $96,000 for the reporting period.
  On August 8 ScotiaBank kept the company rating at “Sector Outperformer” but lowered the price target  to $11.00 from $12.50. July 17 investment analysts at CIBC left the company rating at “Sector Outperform” and lowered the price expectation from $12.00 to $11.50.        Advertisement






 On April 15 CIBC held the company rating at “Sector Perform” but raised the price expectation from $11.00 to $11.50.
 The company is now down by -1.64% since yesterday’s close of $2.44.  Company chares are trading at $2.40 which is marginally lower than the 50 day moving average which is $2.81 and which is just a bit below the 200 day moving average of $3.67.  The 50 day moving average went down by -14.45% and the 200 day average was down $-1.27. 
 As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $-0.57 and is estimated to be $-0.32 for the current year with 49,317,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $-0.11 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $-0.52. 
 Bellatrix Exploration Ltd. engages in the acquisition, exploration, development, and production of oil and natural gas reserves in the provinces of Alberta, British Columbia, and Saskatchewan. It primarily focuses on developing its two core resource plays, the Cardium and the Notikewin/Falher intervals in Western Canada. The company was founded in 2000 and is based in Calgary, Canada..
